meanings.definition: To surpass in trading or exchanging goods or services.
meanings.sent1: She outtraded her friend by getting a better deal on the toy.
meanings.sent2: The experienced negotiator outtraded the novice in the business deal.
meanings.sent3: The clever shopper outtraded the store owner by finding a hidden discount.
meanings.sent4: His quick thinking outtraded the competition in the stock market.
meanings.sent5: The skilled trader outtraded everyone with his strategic moves.

meanings.definition: To have engaged in trading or exchanging goods or services more successfully than someone else.
meanings.sent1: They outtraded their rivals by securing a lucrative contract.
meanings.sent2: The company outtraded its competitors by offering better customer service.
meanings.sent3: The siblings playfully outtraded each other in their lemonade stand sales.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outtraded any obstacles in her path to success.
meanings.sent5: The team outtraded all expectations with their innovative marketing strategy.
